main event: A round, basketball-sized object with black spots and exhaust was observed moving, rolling, and circling in the sky for 10 minutes.
interesting points: The object emitted a black exhaust that was half the size of the object.
The object was observed behind clouds at times.
The witness used binoculars to observe the object.
Weather conditions at the time included clear skies and various wind speeds and directions up to 45,000 feet.
The report concludes that the object was a possible balloon with a package.
